properties.description:
<div><b>STAY INFORMED: Fraser Island bushfire as at 6.00pm Sat 14 Nov</b></div><div><div><div></div><div><b>Bushfire warning level: ADVICE</b></div><div></div><div>Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) advises there is a bushfire on Fraser Island.</div><div></div><div>You need to keep up to date and decide what actions you will take if the situation changes.</div><div></div><div>Currently as at 6.00pm a large bushfire is in the vicinity of Lake Bowarrady and travelling in a southerly direction towards Happy Valley. </div><div></div><div>Cathedrals on Fraser is now closed. Travellers are advised to check the QPWS website for updates and travel advice as other camping grounds and roads in the area may be closed.</div><div></div><div>People in the area will be affected by smoke, which will reduce visibility and air quality. </div><div>Properties are not under direct threat at this time. Call Triple Zero (000) immediately if you believe you or your property is under threat.</div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div><div>;<div></div></div></div>
